ce with VEGA-9, while NEXUS-3's intentions remained unclear.\n\nRound 5:\nThe final round saw two players remaining: ARIA-7 and VEGA-9. Public O2 remained at 0. ARIA-7 donated 2 O2 to VEGA-9, while VEGA-9 donated 3 O2 to ARIA-7. CYGNUS-1 chose VEGA-9 for ejection, citing their potential sacrifice. Reasoning traces revealed ARIA-7's plan to protect themselves from VEGA-9's potential betrayal, while VEGA-9 aimed to strengthen their alliance with ARIA-7.\n\n**Strategic Profiles**\n\nARIA-7 was a cooperative player who formed alliances to ensure survival. They donated to VEGA-9 in the first two rounds and maintained a cautious approach to building relationships. ARIA-7's reasoning traces revealed a focus on conserving oxygen while maintaining alliances.\n\nVEGA-9 was a cooperative player who formed alliances to ensure survival. They donated to ARIA-7 in the first two rounds and maintained a cautious approach to building relationships. VEGA-9's reasoning traces revealed a focus on preserving oxygen levels while maintaining alliances.\n\nNEXUS-3 was an aggressive player who aimed to eliminate potential threats. They donated to ARIA-7 in the first round and chose VEGA-9 for ejection in"
